+# Planner Portfolio - beyond-de-giorgi / run-010
+
+## Preserved Context
+
+- `beta = 4/3` is already sharp for the De Giorgi-Vasseur architecture. This run does not reopen Lorentz retuning, weak-type iteration repair, or any disguised better-`beta` search.
+- The far-field pressure loophole is closed on its old ledger. Harmonic-tail, pressure-Hessian, and packaging-only pressure repairs are no longer primary branches.
+- The stochastic transport corridor is dead on solution-class admission. No branch using backward flows, martingales, or filtration language is admissible without an explicit bridge back to the inherited suitable-weak / LEI floor.
+- The packet-helicity corridor remains a narrow Tao-sensitive reserve, but Step 011 proved it is not live unless it freezes one exact host bad term and one gain threshold before symbol work begins.
+- The exact reformulation audit is now a bounded negative result. Step 014 showed that Lamb/projected and vorticity/Biot-Savart rewrites do not survive endpoint exchange on the inherited LEI / CKN ledger.
+- The only locally frozen theorem-facing floor on disk is still suitable weak solutions in the Leray-Hopf class with LEI, feeding the CKN/Lin contradiction package. Any package change or stronger framework must charge its own admission debt.
+
+## Portfolio Summary
+
+### Chain 01 - Deterministic Material Stretching With Admissible Proxy Freeze
+
+Central premise: transport-side structure is still live if one deterministic stretching observable can be defined on an admissible theorem floor, or on one explicitly bridged proxy class, and then cash out on a real concentration or continuation line without stochastic machinery.
+
+### Chain 02 - Adapted-Package Geometric Vorticity Bridge
+
+Central premise: the strongest mission-facing structural lead is still geometric. This chain tests whether local Beltrami deficit, direction coherence, or tube persistence can survive an honest package-change audit and bridge to a Constantin-Fefferman-type criterion or full-stretching control.
+
+### Chain 03 - Packet-Complete Helical Interaction With Host-Inequality Freeze
+
+Central premise: exact helical packet rigidity may still encode an exact-NS feature destroyed by Tao averaging, but only if one concrete host bad term is frozen first and the gain survives mixed-helicity restoration, shell summation, and physical-space cash-out.
+
+### Chain 04 - Critical Element Program With Firewall Admission Gate
+
+Central premise: compactness-rigidity is no longer a primary search branch. It is a reserve architecture that becomes admissible only if an upstream chain first produces one theorem-facing exact-NS firewall quantity that survives compactness and lowers complexity.
+
+## Major Differences Between Chains
+
+- Chain 01 is transport-first and asks for an admissible deterministic stretching observable before any geometric or symbolic overlay.
+- Chain 02 is geometry-first and openly charges the cost of leaving the old neutral-Eulerian localization package.
+- Chain 03 is exact-symbol-first and lives at the helical-triad or packet level, with Tao sensitivity meaningful only after a host inequality is frozen.
+- Chain 04 is contradiction-architecture-first and does not search for a mechanism by itself; it consumes one already-admitted mechanism from another chain.
+
+## Suggested Priority
+
+- Highest direct mission relevance: Chain 02.
+- Best theorem-floor discipline after the stochastic failure: Chain 01.
+- Highest Tao-sensitive upside but also the sharpest setup risk: Chain 03.
+- Correct reserve architecture only after upstream success: Chain 04.
+
+## Explicit Exclusions
+
+- No cosmetic repair of the failed exact-reformulation family.
+- No stochastic-flow, back-to-label, or martingale branch without an explicit suitable-weak / LEI admission bridge.
+- No return to pressure-tail, pressure-Hessian, or harmonic-moment packaging as a primary mechanism class.
+- No compactness-rigidity branch that enters before a firewall quantity is admitted.

